<TITLE> Comilla scrap dealer dies as 'junk' explodes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Comilla, June 11 (bdnews24.com)A Comilla scrap dealer died after a metal object exploded in his shop Wednesday, police said. Brahmanpara police chief Yunus Ali said the explosion occurred at about 9.30 am in the shop of Billal Hossain, tearing Billal's legs away and injuring a boy of 15 and a 65 year-old man. The grievously wounded Billal was first taken to Brahmanpara Upazila Health Complex and then transferred to Comilla Medical College Hospital, where the he succumbed to his injuries. Quoting eye witnesses, the police chief said Billal was "hammering at a round scrap metal object when the thing detonated, injuring him and the two others in the shop". The two injured were admitted to CMCH for treatment. None could ascertain the type of explosive device so far, police said. Comilla police superintendent Imtiaz Ahmed and RAB officers rushed to the spot after the accident. Investigation into the mishap is ongoing, said Yunus. bdnews2
